    </div>

    <p>Of these four, daily protein intake is the one you can act on starting today. It directly feeds the tissue BMI can't see. And it's the variable most men over 50 are getting wrong — not through laziness, but through not having the right number in front of them.</p>

    <p>The <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/sarcopenia-men-over-40/" style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">muscle you're losing to sarcopenia</a> doesn't show up on a BMI chart. It shows up years later — in your strength, your metabolism, your balance, and your resilience. By then, BMI will still say you're fine.</p>

